# 📰 AI News Agent — Professional .gitignore
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# WHY WE USE A .gitignore FILE:
#   When you share your code on GitHub, you want to upload ONLY your raw source
#   code. You do not want to upload security credentials, local configuration,
#   temporary compiler files, or editor-specific settings.
#
#   This file tells Git which files and folders to completely ignore.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── 1. Security & Secrets (CRITICAL) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# NEVER commit your actual API keys, passwords, or emails to GitHub.
# Local environment secrets live in '.env'. The public copy '.env.example' is safe.
.env

# ── 2. Python Runtime Cache ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When you run Python, it compiles your code into .pyc files inside __pycache__.
# These are machine-specific binary files and are completely redundant.
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.pytest_cache/

# ── 3. Virtual Environments ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Virtual environments contain the downloaded copies of dependencies (requests, jinja2).
# Other developers will download these themselves using 'requirements.txt'.
venv/
.venv/
env/
ENV/

# ── 4. Runtime Logs & Artifacts ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Logs are generated by your app dynamically. We do not want to track historical runs.
# Local template previews (generated by preview_email.py) are also excluded.
logs/
email_preview.html

# ── 5. IDE / Text Editors ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# IDE settings folders contain user-specific display and window layout configs.
.vscode/
.idea/
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.swp

# ── 6. OS Temporary Files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# System-generated metadata files that serve no purpose in code repositories.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
